      <abstract id="aspace_6d854c0fd5e0f1c67276d45ca6014742">American Veterans for Peace (AVP) was founded in 1951 to oppose American participation in the Korean War. The AVP opposed militarism and supported improved Soviet relations and a progressive social agenda. The group published <title render="italic">Progressive Veteran</title> (later <title render="italic">Vet's Voice</title>). The collection includes correspondence, ephemera, internal documents, petitions, public statements, and newsletters created by the AVP and other progressive organizations.</abstract>
      <langmaterial id="aspace_ed1f99981a48142502380677986031a4">Materials are in English</langmaterial>
    </did>
