    <scopecontent id="aspace_cefcb0b96bc6de0f9eb4d41a925c7f58">
      <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
      <p>The collection contains correspondence, primarily between New York chapter co-chairs Paul Green and Norman Wagner, as well as ephemera, internal documents, and petitions and public statements. It also includes AVP newsletters and the newsletters of other progressive organizations, including foreign veterans' organizations. There are files on two annual AVP events: Elbe River Day, commemorating the meeting of American and Soviet troops in 1945, and AVP's art show (the file includes several photographs). Other materials document the campaign against the 1951 film <title render="italic">Desert Fox</title>; the U.S. Post Office's suppression of <title render="italic">Vet's Voice</title>; the activities of an allied organization, the American Women for Peace (including copies of two issues of its monthly newsletter, <title render="italic">The Peacemaker</title>); and the activities of the Australian Legion of Ex-Servicemen and Women.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <userestrict id="aspace_c702d1324d151fcb9363efaa56b17c32">
